summary: Lindsay Lohan returns to the screen in "Our Little Secret," a Christmas rom-com that has received mixed reviews. While the Variety review praises the film for achieving the "full Netflix cookie-cutter" experience, Screen Rant suggests that it lacks both comedy and romance. The New York Post notes an improvement from Lohan's previous Netflix movies. The Guardian sees it as a "minor win," while Forbes highlights the premiere on the streaming platform. Page Six covers Lohan's press tour looks, TheWrap provides a cast and character guide, House Beautiful showcases the Atlanta farmhouse, and Roger Ebert offers a movie review. The Daily Beast shares an insider's perspective on acting in the film.

NJ.com provided a review of Taco Bell's Caramel Apple Empanada, offering insights based on personal experience. Finally, Parade Magazine offers guidance on common pie problems and solutions.

name: Gonzaga basketball
summary: In a thrilling overtime match, West Virginia's men's basketball team upset No. 3 Gonzaga. Indiana University and Gonzaga, ranked third and fourth in the Coaches Poll, are scheduled to face off in Game 6 of the Battle 4 Atlantis tournament. West Virginia is set to encounter No. 3 Gonzaga in an afternoon showdown at the same tournament. Meanwhile, Gonzaga has ascended to the top spot in the KenPom rankings. The team will face West Virginia in the opening match of the Battle 4 Atlantis tournament. Odds and betting suggestions for the encounter between West Virginia and No. 3 Gonzaga are available, while television and streaming details for the Indiana vs. Gonzaga Battle 4 Atlantis match have been released. Gonzaga's big men, Graham Ike and Braden Huff, have been dominating opposition defenses, providing opponents with little respite.
